:iune:batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01:data:sn94054571:00332897962:1949033001:0524/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/iune/batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01/data/sn94054571/00332897962/1949033001/0525.pdf", "segment_count": 14, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn94054571/1949-03-30/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/iune/batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01/data/sn94054571/00332897962/1949033001/0525.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:iune:batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01:data:sn94054571:00332897962:1949033001:0524/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/iune/batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01/data/sn94054571/00332897962/1949033001/0525.pdf", "segment_count": 14, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn94054571/1949-03-30/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/iune/batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01/data/sn94054571/00332897962/1949033001/0525.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn94054571/1949-03-30/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["iune_cinnabar_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/illinois/", "2/united states/illinois/lake county/", "3/united states/illinois/lake county/zion/"], "contributor": ["university of illinois at urbana-champaign library, urbana, il"], "date": "1949-03-30", "dates": ["1949-03-30"], "description": ["PRETTY MARCH WEDDING Mrs Gregory Rice Photo by John Paul Cut Courtesy Waukegan NewsSun Miss Elizabeth Norris Me haffey and E Gregory Rice were united in holy wedlock at a pretty March wedding in Zion Chapel on the evening of March 5th 1949 Overseer An ton Darms was the officiating clergyman Miss Mehaffey is the eldest daughter of Mr and Mrs John A MeHaffey of Zion Hotel Zion Illinois while the brides husband is the younger son of Mr and Mrs Rollin Rice of Toulon Illinois The Chapel altar was deli cately decorated with baskets of white glads grouped be tween graceful palms and ferns while the candelabra on the altar as well as those which flanked the aisle were festooned with streamers of white glads in ivy each mount ed by a large white satin bow The bride entered on the arm of her father in an ivory slipper satin gown with illu sion neckline and a full length train Her threetier illusion veil fell from a tiara of satin and pearls Her bridal flowers consisted of a shower cascade of gardenias and garlands of white hyacinth blossoms and ivy The maid of honor and the bridesmaids entered in"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-05-21T10:17:55.573Z", "group": ["ndnp/iune", "university-of-illinois-at-urbana-champaign-library-urbana-il-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn94054571/1949-03-30/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:iune:batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01:data:sn94054571:00332897962:1949033001:0525/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=400&w=283", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:iune:batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01:data:sn94054571:00332897962:1949033001:0525/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=800&w=567", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/iune/batch_iune_cinnabar_ver01/data/sn94054571/00332897962/1949033001/0525.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["zion", "illinois", "lake county", "united states"], "location_city": ["zion"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["lake county"], "location_state": ["illinois"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["9", "0", "8", "3", "7